==English==

===Etymology===
{{L.}} [[aedilis]], ''[[commissioner]] or [[magistrate]]''

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''aedile'''
#(''in rhe Roman republic'') An elected official who was responsible for the maintenance of public buildings and the regulation of festivals; also supervised markets and the supply of grain and water.

